<subSubSection id="24CB1080FF9CFFC2FAB2AE6C850EFDFD" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C6E430BFF9CFFC2FAB2AE6C850EFDFD" blockId="40.[151,1437,150,537]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2FAB2AE6C815EFEF8" bold="true" box="[199,315,258,284]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Remarks.</emphasis>
Previous records from the coast of 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FF9CFFC2F8BDAE6C835CFEF8" box="[712,825,258,284]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
include Ubatuba, in Pier do 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FF9CFFC2FE0DAE6D84D0FEF9" box="[1144,1205,259,285]" country="Portugal" name="Porto" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Porto</collectingRegion>
in Itaguá (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2FF59AE6C8160FEA5" author="Moraes, I. R. R. &amp; Bergamasco, G. R. &amp; Santos, R. C. &amp; Antunes, M. &amp; Soledade, G. O. &amp; Costa, R. C. &amp; Castilho, A. L." pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="444 - 446" refId="ref70776" refString="Moraes, I. R. R., Bergamasco, G. R., Santos, R. C., Antunes, M., Soledade, G. O., Costa, R. C. &amp; Castilho, A. L. (2020 b) New record of the sponge-dwelling shrimp Typton distinctus Chace, 1972 (Decapoda: Caridea: Palaemonidae) in Sao Paulo State, Brazil. Zootaxa, 4763 (3), 444 - 446. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4763.3.10" type="journal article" year="2020">
Moraes 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2FFFDAE6D80D1FEA4" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2020b
</bibRefCitation>
). It is found in shallow waters associated with sponges (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2F904AE48839FFEA4" author="Chace, F. A. Jr." box="[881,1018,294,320]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 179" refId="ref57454" refString="Chace, F. A. Jr. (1972) The shrimps of the Smithsonian-Bredin Caribbean Expeditions with a summary of the West-Indian shal- low-water species (Crustacea: Decapoda: Natantia). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 98, 1 - 179. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00810282.98" type="journal article" year="1972">Chace 1972</bibRefCitation>
; Ramos-Porto &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2FECEAE488528FEA4" author="Coelho, P. A. &amp; Ramos-Porto, M." box="[1211,1357,294,320]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="387 - 392" refId="ref58648" refString="Coelho, P. A. &amp; Ramos-Porto, M. (1998) Malacostraca-Eucarida. Palinuridae. In: Young, P. S. (Ed.), Catalog of Crustacea from Brazil, Museu Nacional, Rio de Janeiro, 6, pp. 387 - 392" type="journal article" year="1998">Coelho 1998</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2FF2DAE488174FE80" author="Vieira, R. R. R. &amp; Ferreira, R. S. &amp; D'Incao, F." pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref82079" refString="Vieira, R. R. R., Ferreira, R. S. &amp; D'Incao, F. (2012) Pontoniinae (Crustacea: Decapoda: Caridea) from Brazil with taxonomic key. Zootaxa, 3149 (1), 1 - 38. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3149.1.1" type="journal article" year="2012">
Vieira 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2FAE2AE2580AAFE80" box="[151,207,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2FB6EAE24819CFE81" author="Pachelle, P. P. G. &amp; Anker, A. &amp; Tavares, M." box="[283,505,330,357]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="317 - 322" refId="ref72249" refString="Pachelle, P. P. G., Anker, A. &amp; Tavares, M. (2015) New and additional records of the sponge shrimp genus Typton Costa, 1844 (Decapoda: Palaemonidae) from the Brazilian coast. Papeis Avulsos de Zoologia, 55, 317 - 322. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 0031 - 1049.2015.55.22" type="journal article" year="2015">
Pachelle 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2FBF4AE2581DDFE80" box="[385,440,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2F870AE258282FE81" author="Moraes, I. R. R. &amp; Bergamasco, G. R. &amp; Santos, R. C. &amp; Antunes, M. &amp; Soledade, G. O. &amp; Costa, R. C. &amp; Castilho, A. L." box="[517,743,330,357]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="444 - 446" refId="ref70776" refString="Moraes, I. R. R., Bergamasco, G. R., Santos, R. C., Antunes, M., Soledade, G. O., Costa, R. C. &amp; Castilho, A. L. (2020 b) New record of the sponge-dwelling shrimp Typton distinctus Chace, 1972 (Decapoda: Caridea: Palaemonidae) in Sao Paulo State, Brazil. Zootaxa, 4763 (3), 444 - 446. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4763.3.10" type="journal article" year="2020">
Moraes 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2F82AAE2582F2FE80" box="[607,663,330,356]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2020b
</bibRefCitation>
). In general, shrimps of the genus dwell deep in sponge canals (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2FAEAAE008138FE6C" author="Duris, Z. &amp; Horka, I. &amp; Juracka, P. J. &amp; Petrusek, A. &amp; Sandford, F." box="[159,349,366,392]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="21987" refId="ref61556" refString="Duris, Z., Horka, I., Juracka, P. J., Petrusek, A. &amp; Sandford, F. (2011) These squatters are not innocent: the evidence of parasitism in sponge-inhabiting shrimps. PLoS ONE, 6, e 21987. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0021987" type="journal article" year="2011">
Duris 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2FA90AE018178FE6C" box="[229,285,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2FB12AE008248FE6C" author="Anker, A. &amp; Pachelle, P. P. &amp; Leray, M." box="[359,557,366,392]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="267 - 295" refId="ref53156" refString="Anker, A., Pachelle, P. P. &amp; Leray, M. (2021) Two new species of Typton Costa, 1844 from tropical American waters, with taxonomic notes on T. tortugae McClendon, 1911 and a new record of T. granulosus Ayon-Parente, Hendrickx &amp; Galvan- Villa, 2015 (Decapoda: Caridea: Palaemonidae). Zootaxa, 4950 (2), 267 - 295. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4950.2.3" type="journal article" year="2021">
Anker 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2FBC6AE01818EFE6C" box="[435,491,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2021
</bibRefCitation>
). Probably due to these, its small size (carapace length: 
<quantity id="AB29EEEEFF9CFFC2FEECAE008558FE6D" box="[1177,1341,366,393]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.12" metricValueMax="2.71" metricValueMin="1.53" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.12" valueMax="2.71" valueMin="1.53">1.53–2.71 mm</quantity>
) and the relationship among the shrimp’s color and the sponge host (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2F95FAEFC8468FE49" author="Moraes, I. R. R. &amp; Bergamasco, G. R. &amp; Santos, R. C. &amp; Antunes, M. &amp; Soledade, G. O. &amp; Costa, R. C. &amp; Castilho, A. L." box="[810,1037,402,429]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="444 - 446" refId="ref70776" refString="Moraes, I. R. R., Bergamasco, G. R., Santos, R. C., Antunes, M., Soledade, G. O., Costa, R. C. &amp; Castilho, A. L. (2020 b) New record of the sponge-dwelling shrimp Typton distinctus Chace, 1972 (Decapoda: Caridea: Palaemonidae) in Sao Paulo State, Brazil. Zootaxa, 4763 (3), 444 - 446. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4763.3.10" type="journal article" year="2020">
Moraes 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2F9F3AEFD83D8FE48" box="[902,957,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2020b
</bibRefCitation>
), it is hard to sample. There is available material from 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FF9CFFC2FB19AED881B8FE34" box="[364,477,438,464]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">São Paulo</collectingRegion>
coast in other collections such as MZUSP 40095 and 40096, and it is deposited in the Biological Collection from 
<collectingRegion id="AE158DE9FF9CFFC2FBB8AEB48218FE10" box="[461,637,474,500]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">São Paulo State</collectingRegion>
University—Zoology Department, Botucatu-SP (
<bibRefCitation id="08403EFAFF9CFFC2FEDEAEB485F4FE10" author="Moraes, I. R. R. &amp; Almeida, A. O. &amp; Cobo, V. J. &amp; Alves, D. F. R. &amp; Davanso, T. M. &amp; Castilho, A. L." box="[1195,1425,474,500]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" pagination="616 - 631" refId="ref70685" refString="Moraes, I. R. R., Almeida, A. O., Cobo, V. J., Alves, D. F. R., Davanso, T. M. &amp; Castilho, A. L. (2020 a) Biodiversity of caridean shrimps on rocky bottoms of two preserved islands on the southeastern Brazilian coast. Marine Biology Research, 16 (8 - 9), 616 - 631. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 17451000.2020.1864830" type="journal article" year="2020">
Moraes 
<emphasis id="5EA59F19FF9CFFC2FF7DAEB58525FE10" box="[1288,1344,474,500]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">et al.</emphasis>
2020a
</bibRefCitation>
). Sequences accession number (GenBank): CCDB 6713—16S (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FF9CFFC2F925AE9083BDFDFC" box="[848,984,510,536]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OM720040" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">OM720040</accessionNumber>
), COI (
<accessionNumber id="7382DEE8FF9CFFC2FE5CAE9084C8FDFD" box="[1065,1197,510,537]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/OM672405" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">OM672405</accessionNumber>
) (present study).
</paragraph>
